sunny windy training conducted for 3 hours with Jeramiah Schieffenbein.
windy overcast 1.5 inches of rain the last 10 days .weeds starting to appear on surface and much algae in the water. A above average number of Great Blue Heron have been sited lately.
last rain 3.5 inches 8 days ago sunny 70 degrees with a slight breeze
samples were taking in secondary deep hole were ice fisherman are concentrated.
sample was taken in 19 feet of water . I wanted to test were the greatest concetration of ice shacks were.
Above normal temps.in the month of May. Also much more floating algea than normal. A strong emergence of eurasian milfoil also.
very windy and continued heavy rains in recent weeks. Much eurasion milfoil appearing
Continued heavy rain in July  greater than  8 times the average . water is murky water level is high. Much eurasion milfoil . More lilly pads on the lake . July had very good fishing
very green water. A smell of algae was noticed for the first time.
There is and has been extremely deep snow cover on the lake for the last two weeks.

very windy-rain yesterdayand   we have had unseasonably cold spring . some bullheads have washed ashore and watwer continues to be very murky. Water color turned dark last fall . water quality was very poor all winter and continues this spring.
Water continues very poor clarity. A fish kill of 200 crappies was reported. A soil bacteria was determined the cause.
Water is very green. Much eurasian milfoil.

We are havin trouble with the D/O tester.Water samples have been sent in. The lake continues to be extremely murky. The Eurasian Milfoil is as bad as it ever has been. On the good side there is a very large presence of lily pads.This will be my last entry and it is my opinion this lake continues to deteriorate in both water quality- D/O levels and a almost non existant plant life. I believe the DNR must intervene soon or risk a large fish die off and algae will take over the lake.We have done every possible thing the DNR has ask of us over the last ten years and spent much of our own and taxpayer money with absolutly no results or even any hope of any solution from the DNR . a very dicouraged and beaten voulenteer . mike good luck to all who love this lake.
Sunny  -  Spotted 4 Loons  Helper Paul Lambrect
Heavy rainfall last night 1.5 inches of rainfall
